1
00:00:50,541 --> 00:00:53,875
[VENTURI] Attention crew, I've
learned the People of Metus


2
00:00:53,958 --> 00:00:55,833
have successfully
obtained the Fifth Note.


3
00:00:55,916 --> 00:00:57,250
[CREWMEN murmur]

4
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,666
I'm sure they'll use it to
increase their firepower.

5
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:01,333
I imagine they'll be
sending a stream

6
00:01:01,416 --> 00:01:03,625
of new weapons to attack us.

7
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:06,291
The sad truth is, we've
lost too many of our own

8
00:01:06,375 --> 00:01:08,541
over the past 20 years.

9
00:01:08,625 --> 00:01:12,583
The time to put a stop to that
and reclaim our power is now.

10
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:15,708
Mark my words, today we will
give those Copy Humans

11
00:01:15,791 --> 00:01:18,291
their own bloody
crosses to bear!

12
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:20,458
Never forget our purpose here.

13
00:01:20,541 --> 00:01:22,833
The <i>Tiramisu</i> is
Earth's last hope!

14
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,500
You hear me, Ensign Ichinose?

15
00:01:25,583 --> 00:01:27,083
[CREWMEN murmur]

16
00:01:27,166 --> 00:01:28,666
He isn't here, Captain.

17
00:01:28,750 --> 00:01:30,416
I went looking for him earlier.

18
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:32,833
My guess is he's hanging
out in his cockpit.

19
00:01:32,916 --> 00:01:35,125
Why am I not surprised by this?

20
00:01:35,208 --> 00:01:38,666
[VENTURI] What the hell
is he doing in there?

21
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,666
[NARRATOR]
Subaru was feeling quite festive

22
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:43,583
and decided to deck his
halls in the unlikely case

23
00:01:43,666 --> 00:01:45,666
of a space Christmas Party.

24
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,333
Hey, Soob.

25
00:01:47,416 --> 00:01:48,791
Whoa, you decorated.

26
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:50,125
Sortie time.

27
00:01:50,208 --> 00:01:51,541
Unfamiliar craft.

28
00:01:51,625 --> 00:01:52,666
Maybe a new model.

29
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,291
Roger that.

30
00:01:54,375 --> 00:01:57,958
[SUBARU] Freakin' Grinches.
They're ruining my Silent Night.

31
00:01:58,583 --> 00:02:00,791
[SUBARU] Shigeko!
I'm takin' the D Shield.

32
00:02:00,875 --> 00:02:02,208
The hell you are!

33
00:02:02,291 --> 00:02:04,333
Ya have to ask first, and
I'm not done adjusting it,

34
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:05,541
so my answer's no!

35
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:08,000
[SUBARU] Okay, thanks!
I'll bring it back!

36
00:02:10,541 --> 00:02:13,833
[NARRATOR]
And now, a Christmas memory.

37
00:02:13,916 --> 00:02:16,291
[BOY 6A]
Mama, is Santa Claus real?

38
00:02:16,375 --> 00:02:17,541
[MOM 6A]
Of course he is!

39
00:02:17,625 --> 00:02:19,583
But only good kids
like you get to see him!

40
00:02:19,666 --> 00:02:20,625
[BOY 6A]
Really?

41
00:02:20,708 --> 00:02:22,375
[ISUZU]
Makes you miss Mom, huh?

42
00:02:22,458 --> 00:02:23,708
Me, too.

43
00:02:23,791 --> 00:02:25,291
I wasn't thinking about her.

44
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:28,041
Those lights are just
really pretty. Look.

45
00:02:28,125 --> 00:02:29,583
[ISUZU]
Yeah, they're pretty.

46
00:02:29,666 --> 00:02:31,041
Pretty stupid.


47
00:02:31,125 --> 00:02:32,291
Come on, let's go.


48
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:34,416
I don't want Dad to
chew us out again.


49
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:42,041
[NARRATOR]
Little Subaru loved Christmas,

50
00:02:42,125 --> 00:02:44,666
but he always had
to enjoy it from afar.

51
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:47,083
It was never celebrated
in his home.

52
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:52,083
So this is the new model.

53
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,416
[SUBARU] That's right,
just keep shooting!

54
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,625
Go!

55
00:02:56,708 --> 00:02:59,541
Christmas Illumination!

56
00:02:59,625 --> 00:03:01,166
Huh? Whddaya think?

57
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:02,541
Feelin' merry?

58
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:05,500
Check this out! I made
a Santa on the D shield!

59
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:07,541
[NARRATOR] Around the
holidays, it didn't matter

60
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:09,291
if they were friend or foe,

61
00:03:09,375 --> 00:03:12,500
Subaru wanted people to marvel
at his Christmas lights.

62
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:13,958
It stopped shooting.

63
00:03:14,041 --> 00:03:14,958
Never mind!

64
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:15,916
Guess not!

65
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,208
All right, fine!

66
00:03:17,291 --> 00:03:18,958
You asked for it!

67
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:25,083
Merry Christmas,
ya filthy animal.

68
00:03:25,166 --> 00:03:27,000
[INTERCOM VOICE 1A]
Subaru has defeated the enemy!

69
00:03:27,083 --> 00:03:28,000
[VENTURI gasps]

70
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:29,375
[SUBARU]
♪ Joy to the World! ♪

71
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:30,833
[INTERCOM VOICE 1A] He's now
circling us with a bunch

72
00:03:30,916 --> 00:03:32,875
of sparkling lights!

73
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:34,666
[SUBARU]
I forgot the rest.

74
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:37,583
I don't give a damn if
he shot down the enemy!

75
00:03:37,666 --> 00:03:39,958
He shouldn't be
having fun out there!

76
00:03:40,041 --> 00:03:42,375
[NARRATOR] Subaru's heart
was filled with joy,

77
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:45,666
but the crew didn't share
his Christmas spirit.

78
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:48,291
He was thrown back
into isolation.

79
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:50,625
[SUBARU]
Hello darkness, my old friend.

80
00:03:50,708 --> 00:03:53,916
I guess I'm not surprised.
But, I miss my cockpit.

81
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:58,083
It's the only salvation I have
from the Tirami-freakin'-su.

82
00:03:58,166 --> 00:03:59,416
[CODY]
Hey, Soob,

83
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,750
it's gonna be awhile until
the catapult is ready.

84
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:04,000
Roger that. Thanks, Cody.

85
00:04:04,083 --> 00:04:05,166
[sighs]

86
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,208
♪♪♪

87
00:04:07,291 --> 00:04:08,541
[SUBARU]
All right.

88
00:04:08,625 --> 00:04:10,833
Guess I should save
before the final battle.

89
00:04:10,916 --> 00:04:12,875
Man, I leveled up hard.

90
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:16,250
And now the power's out.

91
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:17,125
[gasps]

92
00:04:17,208 --> 00:04:18,208
[screams]

93
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:22,000
[SUBARU]
What do you mean it didn't save?

94
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:24,000
What the hell happened?

95
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,875
[SUBARU] Something's
plugged in back here.

96
00:04:26,958 --> 00:04:28,958
This hose must be
using all the power.

97
00:04:29,041 --> 00:04:30,208
[SHIGERUKO]
Don't touch!

98
00:04:30,291 --> 00:04:32,625
I'm using it! What'd I
tell you about asking?

99
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:34,541
Get back in your pod!

100
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:36,291
[NARRATOR] The Durandal's
electrical system

101
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:38,333
had momentarily gone offline.

102
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:39,500
It appeared the culprit

103
00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:41,916
was the mechanic's
powered cleaning suit.

104
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,708
And don't you dare unplug
it when I turn away!

105
00:04:44,791 --> 00:04:46,958
Think I don't know these tricks?

106
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:49,833
[SUBARU]
Oh, no she didn't!

107
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:53,333
Since when does she need a
power-sucking machine like that?

108
00:04:53,416 --> 00:04:55,458
I was in here first,
so you should've asked me

109
00:04:55,541 --> 00:04:58,625
to use the plug!
There is absolutely nothing

110
00:04:58,708 --> 00:05:01,125
on this ship that needs
to be cleaned right now!

111
00:05:01,208 --> 00:05:02,666
[SUBARU groans]

112
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:05,083
When should it be done then?
I'm not stayin' here any later.

113
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:06,958
If you wanna do the
cleaning, I'll let ya.

114
00:05:07,041 --> 00:05:08,458
No, that's okay.

115
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:10,041
[SHIGERUKO] You can use this
machine, but it needs power.

116
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:11,166
No thank you.

117
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:13,333
That's what I thought. Uh?

118
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:16,916
Looks like you got yourself a
little scrape under your eye.

119
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,958
[SUBARU yelps]

120
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:21,666
[SHIGERUKO]
Gimme yer face!

121
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:23,416
Not necessary!
I can barely feel it!

122
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:26,125
[SHIGERUKO] A little spit magic
will fix you right up!

123
00:05:26,208 --> 00:05:30,541
That's disgusting! Go away!

124
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:34,583
[SUBARU]
I've made up my mind.

125
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:37,375
All I need is my sweet Durandal!

126
00:05:37,458 --> 00:05:40,000
Sick of this ship,
and the jerk-faces on it!

127
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:45,125
I'm taking my things and getting
off this barge of losers.

128
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:47,458
One final walk of shame.

129
00:05:47,541 --> 00:05:52,083
Just don't look anyone in the
eye, especially the captain.

130
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:54,041
[SUBARU gasps]

131
00:05:54,125 --> 00:05:55,791
[SUBARU]
What the hell happened in here?

132
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:58,541
[SUBARU]
Lieutenant Leroy. Captain!

133
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:02,916
[CODY] So, you're finally ready
to leave the <i>Tiramisu</i> , huh?

134
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,916
[SUBARU]
Cody? Uh?

135
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,500
What are you doing
on the bridge?

136
00:06:06,583 --> 00:06:09,333
Oh, right, this is the first
time we're talking in person

137
00:06:09,416 --> 00:06:10,583
and not through a monitor.

138
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:12,333
Hey, Pee Pants.

139
00:06:12,416 --> 00:06:13,958
Is this your boyfriend?

140
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,541
Are you serious right now?

141
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,250
That's the operator! Cody!

142
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:19,333
What are you talkin' about?

143
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:20,666
Cody?

144
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:22,666
That sounds like somethin'
out of your spank bank.

145
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,458
I don't know this guy.

146
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:27,250
[SUBARU gasps]
Don't you move!

147
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:29,500
Go ahead. Shoot me.

148
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:31,958
We have plenty of other
bodies copied and stored

149
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:34,625
aboard the mothership
that I can use.

150
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:37,500
Kill me as many times
as you want.

151
00:06:37,583 --> 00:06:38,625
It's sad.

152
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:40,916
I was hoping you'd recognize me.

153
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,750
I've been lonely without you.

154
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:45,541
[gasps] Wha...? No way.

155
00:06:45,625 --> 00:06:48,625
[NARRATOR]
It was Space Age 0157.

156
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:50,833
Please, come with me?

157
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:52,583
I've missed you.

158
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:56,000
How is that possible?

159
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:58,291
Isuzu?

160
00:06:58,375 --> 00:06:59,541
[NARRATOR]
That night,

161
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:03,458
Subaru was reunited with
his long-lost brother.

